OL,6,FMr Mukhey thanked "brave members of
OL,7,Fthe public" who went to his wife's
OL,8,Faide, but said the trial had forced
OL,9,Fhim to confront "deeply troubling"
OL,10,Ffacts about the psychological
OL,11,Fassessments of her killer.
OL,13,FIn a statement issued after the jury
OL,14,Ffound Debella committed the act of
OL,15,Fkilling Ms Mukhey, her family said:
OL,16,F"He was engaging in escalating
OL,17,Fbehaviour outside those assessments,
OL,18,Fincluding acquiring weapons and
OL,19,Fresearching extreme violence `
OL,20,Fbehaviour that ultimately mirrored the
OL,21,Fviolence he later carried out.
